# Phase 16: UI Restoration — Fix Tailwind Regression & Brand Rename - Context

**Gathered:** 2026-04-22
**Status:** Ready for planning

<domain>
## Phase Boundary

Restore Tailwind CSS styling across all frontend pages and rename the application from "AlgoMaster" to "CodeNexus" in all user-facing text. This phase commits in-progress work, completes the design token migration, performs a comprehensive brand rename, and ensures full Chinese localization of the UI.

</domain>

<decisions>
## Implementation Decisions

### Scope & Completion Criteria
- **D-16-01:** Commit the 60 already-modified files as-is — they contain the in-progress styling fixes. The changes ARE the fix.
- **D-16-02:** Verification = `npm run build` succeeds + `npx vitest --run` passes + visual spot-check that pages render with design system tokens (not browser defaults).

### Design Token Migration
- **D-16-03:** Full migration — replace ALL hardcoded color classes (`text-slate-*`, `bg-white`, `border-slate-*`, `text-gray-*`) with semantic design tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `border-border`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.) across all frontend files.
- **D-16-04:** Use the existing oklch-based design system in `index.css` as the source of truth for all color mappings. Light/dark theme support must be maintained.

### Brand Rename
- **D-16-05:** Comprehensive audit — search ALL files for "AlgoMaster" and replace with "CodeNexus". Includes: UI text, page titles, HTML metadata (title, description), comments referencing the brand, config files, error messages.
- **D-16-06:** "CodeNexus" branding already applied in Sidebar and LoginPage — these serve as the reference pattern.

### Chinese Localization
- **D-16-07:** Full Chinese UI — all user-facing text should be in Chinese. Replace remaining English labels (e.g., "Theme", "Language", button text) with Chinese equivalents.
- **D-16-08:** Technical terms (API names, code identifiers, CSS class names) remain in English. Only user-visible text is localized.

### Execution Guidance
- **D-16-09:** When allocating subagents for frontend rewrites, load the design skill files from `frontend-skill/` directory (Linear, Vercel, Supabase references) to guide styling decisions.
- **D-16-10:** Default model for executor subagents: `opus` (Claude Opus) or `glm-5.1`.

### Claude's Discretion
- Exact spacing and typography adjustments
- Which Lucide icon to use when replacing a Material Symbol
- Order of file processing during migration

</decisions>

